&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NECS works across the UK to support health and social care customers in meeting their strategic and operational challenges; improving outcomes and increasing efficiency. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our current customers include local authorities, Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs), a range of healthcare providers, including those that make up STPs and emerging ICSs, and third and private sector organisations. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NECS employs over 1,000 experienced and skilled people across the UK, but as a growing organisation with a diverse range of service offerings we are seeking talented and experienced professionals to join our supply chain. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We recognise that our customers need tailored solutions delivered flexibly, and so it is important for us to be able to draw upon expertise and knowledge from outside our immediate organisation to enhance and potentially expand the range of services offered to our customers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Associates are a valued part of our organisation, with opportunities arising across the country in a range of disciplines; please visit our website for more information on our organisation, our values and the range of services we offer. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in joining us as an Associate please apply today. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
